# Placeholder NATS credentials fixture for the creds-file auth mode spec.
# Replace with a real .creds file generated by nsc when running the creds-file
# auth integration test.
#
# Example (with NATS Security Credentials):
#   nsc add account -n test
#   nsc add user -n testuser
#   nsc generate creds -n testuser > spec/fixtures/nats/test.creds
#
# This placeholder is checked in so the mutual-exclusion spec always has a
# non-nil path to hand to Configuration. The file is intentionally invalid
# for actual NATS connections — the creds-file integration test must replace
# it with real credentials before running.
-----BEGIN NATS USER JWT-----
PLACEHOLDER_JWT_NOT_VALID
------END NATS USER JWT------

-----BEGIN USER NKEY SEED-----
PLACEHOLDER_SEED_NOT_VALID
------END USER NKEY SEED------
